tSapEgressFCInProfPrec.description: The value of tSapEgressFCInProfPrec specifies the precedence value to set for in-profile frames in this forwarding class. The values of tSapEgressFCInProfPrec and tSapEgressFCOutProfPrec must be set to either the default or non-default values for both. An inconsistentValue error is returned if one object is set to the default and other is set to a non-default value. The values of tSapEgressFCInProfDscp and tSapEgressFCOutProfDscp are reset to default values when tSapEgressFCOutProfPrec is set to any value other than default. An inconsistentValue error is returned if this object is set to any value other than its default value when setting tSapEgressFCInProfDscp object or tSapEgressFCOutProfDscp to a value other than their default values.

tSapEgressFCOutProfPrec.name: tSapEgressFCOutProfPrec
tSapEgressFCOutProfPrec.description: The value of tSapEgressFCOutProfPrec specifies the precedence value to set for out-profile frames in this forwarding class. The values of tSapEgressFCInProfPrec and tSapEgressFCOutProfPrec must be be set to either the default or non-default values for both. An inconsistentValue error is returned if one object is set to the default and other is set to a non-default value. The values of tSapEgressFCInProfDscp and tSapEgressFCOutProfDscp are reset to default values when tSapEgressFCOutProfPrec is set to any value other than default. An inconsistentValue error is returned if this object is set to any value other than its default value when setting tSapEgressFCInProfDscp object or tSapEgressFCOutProfDscp to a value other than their default values.

tSapEgressFCQGrp.name: tSapEgressFCQGrp
tSapEgressFCQGrp.description: The value of tSapEgressFCQGrp specifies the tQosEgrQGroupName. When set to a non-default value, this indicates the name of the queue-group to which traffic will be forwarded.

tSapEgressFCPolicer.name: tSapEgressFCPolicer
tSapEgressFCPolicer.description: The value of tSapEgressFCPolicer specifies the SAP Egress Policer identifier. If a corresponding Sap Egress Policer Id does not exist in tSapEgrPolicerTable, an 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned. When tSapEgressFCPolicer is set to its default value, then traffic for this forwarding class will not use policers. When tSapEgressFCPolicer is set to a non-default value, and tSapEgressFCQGrp is set to default, and tSapEgressFCQueue is set to default, then traffic will use the given policer, and then feed into a system determined queue-group queue. When tSapEgressFCPolicer is set to a non-default value, and tSapEgressFCQGrp is set to a non-default value, and tSapEgressFCQueue is set to default, then traffic will use the given policer, and then feed into a queue within the given queue-group according to the appropriate tQosEgrQGroupFCEntry. When tSapEgressFCPolicer is set to a non-default value, and tSapEgressFCQGrp is set to a non-default value, and tSapEgressFCQueue is set to a non-default value, then trafifc will use the given policer, and then feed into the given queue within the given queue-group. When tSapEgressFCPolicer is set to a non-default value, and tSapEgressFCQGrp is set its default value, and tSapEgressFCQueue is set to a non-default value, then trafifc will use the given policer, and then feed into the given local queue.

tSapEgressFCQGrpFC.name: tSapEgressFCQGrpFC
tSapEgressFCQGrpFC.description: The value of tSapEgressFCQGrpFC, when specified, will replace the forwarding class derived from ingress as the forwarding class to use inside the egress queue group. tSapEgressFCQGrpFC is only allowed to be used in conjunction with egress policers, and is mutually exclusive with direct queue-group queue mappings. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if tSapEgressFCQGrpFC is set to a non-default value when tSapEgressFCPolicer is set to default.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueTable.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueTable
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueTable.description: Information about all sap-egress policies' HSMDA queues.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueEntry.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueEntry
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueEntry.description: Information about a particular HSMDA queue for a sap-egress policy. Entries are created by user.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueue.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueue
tSapEgressHsmdaQueue.description: The HSMDA queue ID is used as the secondary index to the table entry.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueRowStatus.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueRowStatus
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueRowStatus.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of entries in the tSapEgressHsmdaQueueTable.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueCIRAdaptn.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueCIRAdaptn
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueCIRAdaptn.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueCIRAdaptn specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational CIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset. This object is obsoleted in 10.0 Release.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueuePIRAdaptn.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueuePIRAdaptn
tSapEgressHsmdaQueuePIRAdaptn.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueuePIRAdaptn specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational PIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueAdminPIR.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueAdminPIR
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueAdminPIR.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueAdminPIR specifies the administrative PIR specified by the user.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueAdminCIR.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueAdminCIR
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueAdminCIR.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueAdminCIR specifies the administrative CIR specified by the user. This object is obsoleted in 10.0 Release.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueSlopePolicy.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueSlopePolicy
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueSlopePolicy.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueSlopePolicy specifies the slope policy specified by the user.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueLastChanged.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueLastChanged
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueLastChanged.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in tSapEgressHsmdaQueueTable.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueWrrWeight.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueWrrWeight
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueWrrWeight.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueWrrWeight specifies the weight with which this queue should parent into the HSMDA scheduler, provided it is not superseded by the Weighted Round Robin (WRR) policy. The weight of each queue determines how much bandwidth that queue gets out of the total rate for the scheduling class.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueMBS.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueMBS
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueMBS.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueMBS specifies the maximum amount of buffer space (in bytes) allowed for this HSMDA queue.

tSapEgressHsmdaQueueBurstLimit.name: tSapEgressHsmdaQueueBurstLimit
tSapEgressHsmdaQueueBurstLimit.description: The value of tSapEgressHsmdaQueueBurstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the queue.

tSapEgressDSCPTable.name: tSapEgressDSCPTable
tSapEgressDSCPTable.description: a list of all DSCP entries for all sap-egress policies.

tSapEgressDSCPEntry.name: tSapEgressDSCPEntry
tSapEgressDSCPEntry.description: Information about a particular DSCP entry for a sap-egress policy. Entries are created by user. Entries are deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile. in the event that one policy has multiple entries, and the tSapEgressDSCP values are the same, only one queue will be created (the queue for the lexicographically first tSapEgressDSCP).

tSapEgressDSCPRowStatus.name: tSapEgressDSCPRowStatus
tSapEgressDSCPRowStatus.description: The value of tSapEgressDSCPRowStatus controls the creation/deletion of rows in this table.

tSapEgressDSCPLastChanged.name: tSapEgressDSCPLastChanged
tSapEgressDSCPLastChanged.description: The value of tSapEgressDSCPLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this table row.

tSapEgressDSCPHsmdaCntrOverride.name: tSapEgressDSCPHsmdaCntrOverride
tSapEgressDSCPHsmdaCntrOverride.description: The value of the object tSapEgressDSCPHsmdaCntrOverride specifies the counter to use for all the traffic that matches the specific DSCP i.e. tSapEgressDSCP. A value of zero implies that the default counters should be used.

tSapEgressDSCPfc.name: tSapEgressDSCPfc
tSapEgressDSCPfc.description: The value of tSapEgressDSCPfc, when specified, will overwrite the forwarding class derived from ingress. The new forwarding class is used for egress remarking and queue mapping decisions.

tSapEgressDSCPprofile.name: tSapEgressDSCPprofile
tSapEgressDSCPprofile.description: The value of tSapEgressDSCPprofile, when provided, specifies the egress classification rule that will overwrite the profile of the packet derived from the ingress. The new profile value is used for egress remarking and queue congestion behavior.

tSapEgressPrecTable.name: tSapEgressPrecTable
tSapEgressPrecTable.description: This table maintains the mapping of a particular precedence value into a forwarding class

tSapEgressPrecEntry.name: tSapEgressPrecEntry
tSapEgressPrecEntry.description: Information about a particular sap-egress policy's IP precedence values to forwarding class mappings. Entries are created and deleted by user. They have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tSapEgressPrecValue.name: tSapEgressPrecValue
tSapEgressPrecValue.description: The value of tSapEgressPrecValue indicates the precedence value for which the mapping is done. It is used as a secondary index for tSapEgressPrecTable.

tSapEgressPrecRowStatus.name: tSapEgressPrecRowStatus
tSapEgressPrecRowStatus.description: The value of tSapEgressPrecRowStatus controls the creation/deletion of rows in this table.

tSapEgressPrecLastChanged.name: tSapEgressPrecLastChanged
tSapEgressPrecLastChanged.description: The value of tSapEgressPrecLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this table row.

tSapEgressPrecHsmdaCntrOverride.name: tSapEgressPrecHsmdaCntrOverride
tSapEgressPrecHsmdaCntrOverride.description: The value of tSapEgressPrecHsmdaCntrOverride specifies the counter to use for all the traffic that matches the specific precedence value i.e. tSapEgressPrecValue. A value of zero implies that the default counters should be used.

tSapEgressPrecFC.name: tSapEgressPrecFC
tSapEgressPrecFC.description: The value of tSapEgressPrecFC, when specified, will overwrite the forwarding class derived from ingress. The new forwarding class is used for egress remarking and queue mapping decisions.

tSapEgressPrecProfile.name: tSapEgressPrecProfile
tSapEgressPrecProfile.description: The value of tSapEgressPrecProfile, when provided, specifies the egress classification rule that will overwrite the profile of the packet derived from the ingress. The new profile value is used for egress remarking and queue congestion behavior.

tSapEgrIPCritTable.name: tSapEgrIPCritTable
tSapEgrIPCritTable.description: This table maintains the entries for matching criteria for IP packets on egress. In release 10.0 and higher, this table can also contain IPv6 criteria.

tSapEgrIPCritEntry.name: tSapEgrIPCritEntry
tSapEgrIPCritEntry.description: Information about a particular egress IP or IPv6 matching criteria entry. Entries are created and deleted by user. They have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tSapEgrIPCritAddrType.name: tSapEgrIPCritAddrType
tSapEgrIPCritAddrType.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritAddrType specifies the index address type this entry should match against.

tSapEgrIPCritIndex.name: tSapEgrIPCritIndex
tSapEgrIPCritIndex.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritIndex specifies the index for a sap-egress IP or IPv6 criteria entry.

tSapEgrIPCritRowStatus.name: tSapEgrIPCritRowStatus
tSapEgrIPCritRowStatus.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of sap-egress IP or IPv6 criteria entries.

tSapEgrIPCritLastChanged.name: tSapEgrIPCritLastChanged
tSapEgrIPCritLastChanged.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tSapEgrIPCritDescription.name: tSapEgrIPCritDescription
tSapEgrIPCritDescription.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritDescription specifies a description of the sap-egress IP or IPv6 criteria entry.

tSapEgrIPCritActionHsmdaCntrOvr.name: tSapEgrIPCritActionHsmdaCntrOvr
tSapEgrIPCritActionHsmdaCntrOvr.description: The value of the object tSapEgrIPCritActionHsmdaCntrOvr specifies the Hsmda counter to use for matching packets. This value will be ignored when the sap-egress policy specified by tSapEgressIndex, is applied to a SAP on a non-Hsmda MDA type. A value of zero implies that the default counters should be used.

tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddrType.name: tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddrType
tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddrType.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddrType specifies the address type of tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddr. If the value of this object is not 'none', it must have the same value as tSapEgrIPCritAddrType.

tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddr.name: tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddr
tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddr.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpAddr specifies the IP or IPv6 address to match with source-IP of the packet.

tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpMask.name: tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpMask
tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpMask.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritSourceIpMask specifies the number of bits of the source IP or IPv6 address to match.

tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddrType.name: tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddrType
tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddrType.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddrType specifies the address type of tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddr. If the value of this object is not 'none', it must have the same value as tSapEgrIPCritAddrType.

tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddr.name: tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddr
tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddr.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritDestIpAddr specifies the IP or IPv6 address to match with destination-IP of the packet.

tSapEgrIPCritDestIpMask.name: tSapEgrIPCritDestIpMask
tSapEgrIPCritDestIpMask.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritDestIpMask specifies the number of bits of the destination IP or IPv6 address to match.

tSapEgrIPCritProtocol.name: tSapEgrIPCritProtocol
tSapEgrIPCritProtocol.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritProtocol specifies the IP protocol or IPv6 next-header to match. The value '-1' is used to disable matching by IP protocol or IPv6 next-header. When this value specifies an IPv6 next-header, since the match criteria only pertains to the last next-header, the following values are not accepted: 0, 43, 44, 50, 51, and 60.

tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue1.name: tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue1
tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue1.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue1 specifies the first TCP/UDP source port value. The value of this object is used according to the value of tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortOperator.

tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue2.name: tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue2
tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue2.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue2 specifies the second TCP/UDP source port value. The value of this object is used according to the value of tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortOperator.

tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortOperator.name: tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortOperator
tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortOperator.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortOperator specifies the manner in which tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue1 and tSapEgrIPCritSourcePortValue2 are to be used.

tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue1.name: tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue1
tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue1.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue1 specifies the first TCP/UDP destination port value. The value of this object is used according to the value of tSapEgrIPCritDestPortOperator.

tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue2.name: tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue2
tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue2.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue2 specifies the second TCP/UDP destination port value. The value of this object is used according to the value of tSapEgrIPCritDestPortOperator.

tSapEgrIPCritDestPortOperator.name: tSapEgrIPCritDestPortOperator
tSapEgrIPCritDestPortOperator.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritDestPortOperator specifies the manner in which tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue1 and tSapEgrIPCritDestPortValue2 are to be used.

tSapEgrIPCritDSCP.name: tSapEgrIPCritDSCP
tSapEgrIPCritDSCP.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritDSCP specifies the DSCP value to match in the packet

tSapEgrIPCritFragment.name: tSapEgrIPCritFragment
tSapEgrIPCritFragment.description: The value of tSapEgrIPCritFragment specifies fragmented packet matching. If the value is 'true', only fragmented packets match. If the value is 'false', only non-fragmented packets match. If the value is 'off', all packets match regardless. This field is only relevant for ipv4. An inconsistentValue error is returned when the value of tSapEgrIPCritFragment is not 'off' and the value of tSapEgrIPCritAddrType is not 'ipv4'.

tSapEgrIPCritActionFC.name: tSapEgrIPCritActionFC
tSapEgrIPCritActionFC.description: tSapEgrIPCritActionFC specifies the forwarding class to be used to classify all the traffic that matches the specific IP or IPv6 criteria. The value ''H indicates that the FC is derived from ingress classification and profiling functions.

tSapEgrIPCritActionProfile.name: tSapEgrIPCritActionProfile
tSapEgrIPCritActionProfile.description: tSapEgrIPCritActionProfile specifies the profile of the traffic that matches the specific IP or IPv6 criteria. The value none indicates that the profile is derived from ingress classification and profiling functions.

tSapEgrPolicerTableLastChanged.name: tSapEgrPolicerTableLastChanged
tSapEgrPolicerTableLastChanged.description: tSapEgrPolicerTableLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to the tSapEgrPolicerTable.

tSapEgrPolicerTable.name: tSapEgrPolicerTable
tSapEgrPolicerTable.description: tSapEgrPolicerTable defines SAP Egress Policer Table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of defining the policers. tSapEgrPolicerTable holds a list of all the policers configured in the managed system. Policers must exist in this table before being referenced by the forwarding class mappings within the queue policy as defined in the tSapEgressFCTable.

tSapEgrPolicerEntry.name: tSapEgrPolicerEntry
tSapEgrPolicerEntry.description: tSapEgrPolicerEntry defines an entry in the tSapEgrPolicerTable. Entries are created/deleted in this table by SNMP sets to tSapEgrPolicerRowStatus.

tSapEgrPolicerId.name: tSapEgrPolicerId
tSapEgrPolicerId.description: tSapEgrPolicerId defines the SAP Egress Policer identifier. It identifies an sap-egress policer in the managed system.

tSapEgrPolicerRowStatus.name: tSapEgrPolicerRowStatus
tSapEgrPolicerRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
tSapEgrPolicerRowStatus.description: tSapEgrPolicerRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tSapEgrPolicerTable.

tSapEgrPolicerLastChanged.name: tSapEgrPolicerLastChanged
tSapEgrPolicerLastChanged.description: tSapEgrPolicerLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime when the entry was last modified.

tSapEgrPolicerDescr.name: tSapEgrPolicerDescr
tSapEgrPolicerDescr.description: tSapEgrPolicerDescr specifies the description of the policer.

tSapEgrPolicerPIRAdaptation.name: tSapEgrPolicerPIRAdaptation
tSapEgrPolicerPIRAdaptation.description: The adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational PIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset.

tSapEgrPolicerCIRAdaptation.name: tSapEgrPolicerCIRAdaptation
tSapEgrPolicerCIRAdaptation.description: The adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational CIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset.

tSapEgrPolicerParent.name: tSapEgrPolicerParent
tSapEgrPolicerParent.description: tSapEgrPolicerParent specifies the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding.

tSapEgrPolicerLevel.name: tSapEgrPolicerLevel
tSapEgrPolicerLevel.description: tSapEgrPolicerLevel specifies the level of priority while feeding the parent.

tSapEgrPolicerWeight.name: tSapEgrPolicerWeight
tSapEgrPolicerWeight.description: tSapEgrPolicerWeight specifies the weight that needs to be used by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding.

tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIR.name: tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIR
tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIR.description: tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIR specifies the administrative PIR specified by the user.

tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIR.name: tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIR
tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIR.description: tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIR specifies the administrative CIR specified by the user.

tSapEgrPolicerStatMode.name: tSapEgrPolicerStatMode
tSapEgrPolicerStatMode.description: tSapEgrPolicerStatMode specifies the mode of statistics collected by this policer.

tSapEgrPolicerMBS.name: tSapEgrPolicerMBS
tSapEgrPolicerMBS.description: The tSapEgrPolicerMBS specifies the high priority 'violate' threshold of PIR leaky bucket of this policer.

tSapEgrPolicerHiPrioOnly.name: tSapEgrPolicerHiPrioOnly
tSapEgrPolicerHiPrioOnly.description: The tSapEgrPolicerHiPrioOnly specifies the percentage of PIR leaky bucket's MBS (maximum burst size) of this policer that is reserved for high priority traffic.

tSapEgrPolicerCBS.name: tSapEgrPolicerCBS
tSapEgrPolicerCBS.description: The tSapEgrPolicerCBS specifies the 'exceed' threshold of the CIR leaky bucket of this policer.

tSapEgrPolicerPktOffset.name: tSapEgrPolicerPktOffset
tSapEgrPolicerPktOffset.description: tSapEgrPolicerPktOffset specifies the packet byte offset for addition of policing information by this policer.

tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIRPercent.name: tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIRPercent
tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIRPercent.description: The administrative PIR percentage, in hundredths of a percent. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIRPercent is set to non-default value when the object tSapEgrPolicerRateType is set to 'kbps'.

tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIRPercent.name: tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIRPercent
tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIRPercent.description: The administrative CIR percentage, in hundredths of a percent. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIRPercent is set to non-default value when the object tSapEgrPolicerRateType is set to 'kbps'.

tSapEgrPolicerRateType.name: tSapEgrPolicerRateType
tSapEgrPolicerRateType.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicerRateType specifies the type of egress policer rate. When the value of the object is set to 'kbps', the egresss policer rates are specified in kbps. The objects tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIRPercent and tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIRPercent will be set to their default values. When the value of the object is set to 'percentOfLocalLimit', the egress policer rates are specified in percentage. The objects tSapEgrPolicerAdminPIR and tSapEgrPolicerAdminCIR will be set to their default values.

tSapEgrPolicerSlopeStartDepth.name: tSapEgrPolicerSlopeStartDepth
tSapEgrPolicerSlopeStartDepth.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicerSlopeStartDepth specifies the percentage of the buffer utilized after which the drop probability starts to rise above 0.

tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxDepth.name: tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxDepth
tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxDepth.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxDepth specifies the percentage of the buffer utilized after which the drop probability is 100 percent. This implies that all packets beyond this point will be dropped.

tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxProb.name: tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxProb
tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxProb.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxProb specifies the drop probability, as a percentage, when the queue depth reaches tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxDepth. The drop increases steadily from 0 at the tSapEgrPolicerSlopeStartDepth up to the tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxProb at the tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMaxDepth.

tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMap.name: tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMap
tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMap.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicerSlopeMap specifies the slope map to be used with this policer.

tSapEgrPolicerAdvCfgPolicy.name: tSapEgrPolicerAdvCfgPolicy
tSapEgrPolicerAdvCfgPolicy.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicerAdvCfgPolicy specifies the name of the advanced configuration policy to be applied with this policer.

tSapEgrPolicerProfileCapped.name: tSapEgrPolicerProfileCapped
tSapEgrPolicerProfileCapped.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicerProfileCapped specifies how the explicit in-profile and undetermined profile traffic should be handled at the egress policer. When the value of tSapEgrPolicerProfileCapped is set to 'true', both explicit in-profile and undetermined profile traffic is honored up to CIR, above which it is marked as out-of-profile. If CIR is set to zero, then all explicit in-profile and undetermined profile packets, along with the explicit out-of-profile packets are marked as out-of-profile. The default behavior when tSapEgrPolicerProfileCapped is set to 'false' is to ignore the CIR output state when an explicit in-profile packet is handled by an egress policer.

tSapEgrPolicyNameTableLastChgd.name: tSapEgrPolicyNameTableLastChgd
tSapEgrPolicyNameTableLastChgd.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicyNameTableLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tSapEgrPolicyNameTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tSapEgrPolicyNameTable.name: tSapEgrPolicyNameTable
tSapEgrPolicyNameTable.description: A table that contains SAP egress policy name information. Entries are created automatically by the system when tSapEgressPolicyName object is set for the SAP egress policy.

tSapEgrPolicyNameEntry.name: tSapEgrPolicyNameEntry
tSapEgrPolicyNameEntry.description: Basic information about a specific SAP egress policy name.

tSapEgrPolicyNameId.name: tSapEgrPolicyNameId
tSapEgrPolicyNameId.description: The value of the object tSapEgrPolicyNameId specifies the policy name associated with this SAP egress policy.

tSapEgrPolicyNameRowStatus.name: tSapEgrPolicyNameRowStatus
tSapEgrPolicyNameRowStatus.description: This value of the object tSapEgrPolicyNameRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tSapEgrPolicyNameLastChanged.name: tSapEgrPolicyNameLastChanged
tSapEgrPolicyNameLastChanged.description: The value of tSapEgrPolicyNameLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tSapEgressDot1pTableLastChanged.name: tSapEgressDot1pTableLastChanged
tSapEgressDot1pTableLastChanged.description: tSapEgressDot1pTableLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to the tSapEgressDot1pTable.

tSapEgressDot1pTable.name: tSapEgressDot1pTable
tSapEgressDot1pTable.description: A table that contains the list of all dot1p entries for all sap-egress policies.

tSapEgressDot1pEntry.name: tSapEgressDot1pEntry
tSapEgressDot1pEntry.description: Information about a particular dot1p match for a sap-egress policy. Entries are created/deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tSapEgressDot1pValue.name: tSapEgressDot1pValue
tSapEgressDot1pValue.description: The value of tSapEgressDot1pValue specifies the dotp value to match in the packet. This value is also used as an index so that for any dot1p value there is only one possible disposition queue and priority.

tSapEgressDot1pRowStatus.name: tSapEgressDot1pRowStatus
tSapEgressDot1pRowStatus.description: tSapEgressDot1pRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tSapEgressDot1pTable.

tSapEgressDot1pLastChanged.name: tSapEgressDot1pLastChanged
tSapEgressDot1pLastChanged.description: The value of tSapEgressDot1pLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry.

tSapEgressDot1pFC.name: tSapEgressDot1pFC
tSapEgressDot1pFC.description: The value of tSapEgressDot1pFC specifies the forwarding class to be used to classify all the traffic that matches the Dot1p value specified by tSapEgressDot1pValue. Unless tSapEgressDot1pFC is specified explicitly, this match will be ignored for classification purposes.

tSapEgressDot1pProfile.name: tSapEgressDot1pProfile
tSapEgressDot1pProfile.description: The value of tSapEgressDot1pProfile specifies the profile to use for packets that match the dot1p value specified by tSapEgressDot1pValue.

tNetworkPolicyEntry.name: tNetworkPolicyEntry
tNetworkPolicyEntry.description: Information about a particular Network Policy. network policy (1) is the default entry. Default Entry is created by the agent, other entries are created by user. Default Entry cannot be modified/deleted. The other entries are deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile. The default Egress FC entries are created as an action of setting the rowstatus.

tNetworkPolicyDescription.name: tNetworkPolicyDescription
tNetworkPolicyDescription.description: tNetworkPolicyDescription holds the description for this policy.

tNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionFC.name: tNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionFC
tNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionFC.description: tNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionFC specifies the default forwarding class to be used while classifying the ingress traffic.

tNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionProfil.name: tNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionProfile
tNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionProfil.description: tNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionProfile specifies the default profile to be used for the ingressing traffic.

tNetworkPolicyEgressRemark.name: tNetworkPolicyEgressRemark
tNetworkPolicyEgressRemark.description: The object tNetworkPolicyEgressRemark specifies if the system will remark the egress packets or not.

tNetworkPolicyLastChanged.name: tNetworkPolicyLastChanged
tNetworkPolicyLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in tNetworkPolicyTable.

tNetworkPolicyIngressLerUseDscp.name: tNetworkPolicyIngressLerUseDscp
tNetworkPolicyIngressLerUseDscp.description: The object has significance only for the label edge routers which should honor the DSCP markings instead of the LSPEXP bits.

tNetworkPolicyEgressRemarkDscp.name: tNetworkPolicyEgressRemarkDscp
tNetworkPolicyEgressRemarkDscp.description: The value of tNetworkPolicyEgressRemarkDscp object specifies whether DSCP bits in the internal IP header should be remarked. This object is valid only when tNetworkPolicyEgressRemark is set to 'true'.

tNetworkIngressDSCPEntry.name: tNetworkIngressDSCPEntry
tNetworkIngressDSCPEntry.description: Information about a dscp map for a network policy. Some default entries are created by the agent for the default network policy (1). These cannot be deleted or modified. Other entries are created/deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tNetworkIngressDSCPProfile.name: tNetworkIngressDSCPProfile
tNetworkIngressDSCPProfile.description: there is no DEFVAL for this object. it must be deliberately set before activating the row.

tNetworkIngressDSCPLastChanged.name: tNetworkIngressDSCPLastChanged
tNetworkIngressDSCPLastChanged.description: timestamp of last change to this row in tNetworkIngressDSCPTable.

tNetworkIngressDot1pEntry.name: tNetworkIngressDot1pEntry
tNetworkIngressDot1pEntry.description: Information about a dot1p map for a network policy. Some default entries are created by the agent for the default network policy (1). These cannot be deleted or modified. Other entries are created/deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tNetworkIngressDot1pProfile.name: tNetworkIngressDot1pProfile
tNetworkIngressDot1pProfile.description: there is no DEFVAL for this object. It must be deliberately set before activating the row.

tNetworkIngressDot1pLastChanged.name: tNetworkIngressDot1pLastChanged
tNetworkIngressDot1pLastChanged.description: timestamp of last change to this row in tNetworkIngressDot1pTable.

tNetworkIngressLSPEXPEntry.name: tNetworkIngressLSPEXPEntry
tNetworkIngressLSPEXPEntry.description: Information about LSP EXP mapping for a network policy. Some default entries are created by the agent for the default network policy (1). These cannot be deleted or modified. Other entries are created/deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tNetworkIngressLSPEXPProfile.name: tNetworkIngressLSPEXPProfile
tNetworkIngressLSPEXPProfile.description: there is no DEFVAL for this object. it must be deliberately set before activating the row.

tNetworkIngressLSPEXPLastChanged.name: tNetworkIngressLSPEXPLastChanged
tNetworkIngressLSPEXPLastChanged.description: timestamp of last change to this row in tNetworkIngressLSPEXPTable.

tNetworkEgressFCTable.name: tNetworkEgressFCTable
tNetworkEgressFCTable.description: Information about all network policies' egress FC traffic disposition.

tNetworkEgressFCEntry.name: tNetworkEgressFCEntry
tNetworkEgressFCEntry.description: Information about a particular network policy's egress per-forwarding-class traffic disposition. Entries are created/deleted as an action of creating/deleting a row in the tNetworkPolicyTable. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tNetworkEgressFCName.name: tNetworkEgressFCName
tNetworkEgressFCName.description: the name of the forwarding class (FC).

tNetworkEgressFCDSCPInProfile.name: tNetworkEgressFCDSCPInProfile
tNetworkEgressFCDSCPInProfile.description: the DSCP to use for in-profile traffic.

tNetworkEgressFCDSCPOutProfile.name: tNetworkEgressFCDSCPOutProfile
tNetworkEgressFCDSCPOutProfile.description: the DSCP to use for out-of-profile traffic.

tNetworkEgressFCLspExpInProfile.name: tNetworkEgressFCLspExpInProfile
tNetworkEgressFCLspExpInProfile.description: the lsp-exp value to use for in-profile traffic.

tNetworkEgressFCLspExpOutProfile.name: tNetworkEgressFCLspExpOutProfile
tNetworkEgressFCLspExpOutProfile.description: the lsp-exp value to use for out-of-profile traffic.

tNetworkEgressFCDot1pInProfile.name: tNetworkEgressFCDot1pInProfile
tNetworkEgressFCDot1pInProfile.description: the Dot1p to use for in-profile traffic.

tNetworkEgressFCDot1pOutProfile.name: tNetworkEgressFCDot1pOutProfile
tNetworkEgressFCDot1pOutProfile.description: the Dot1p to use for out-of-profile traffic.

tNetworkEgressFCLastChanged.name: tNetworkEgressFCLastChanged
tNetworkEgressFCLastChanged.description: timestamp of last change to this row in tNetworkEgressFCTable.

tNetworkEgressFCForceDEValue.name: tNetworkEgressFCForceDEValue
tNetworkEgressFCForceDEValue.description: The value of tNetworkEgressFCForceDEValue specifies the DE value to set for network egress packets in this forwarding class regardless of profile status of the frames. An inconsistentValue error is returned if this object is set to any value other than '-1', when tNetworkEgressFCDEMark object is set to 'false'.

tNetworkEgressFCDEMark.name: tNetworkEgressFCDEMark
tNetworkEgressFCDEMark.description: The value of tNetworkEgressFCDEMark specifies whether to set DE value in the frames of this forwarding class. An inconsistentValue error is returned if this object is set to 'false' when tNetworkEgressFCForceDEValue object is not set to '-1'.

tNetworkEgressFCQGrpQueue.name: tNetworkEgressFCQGrpQueue
tNetworkEgressFCQGrpQueue.description: tNetworkEgressFCQGrpQueue specifies the specific queue from queue-group TIMETRA-VRTR-MIB::vRtrIfQosQGrp to be used for packets in this forwarding class.

tNetworkEgressFCQGrpPolicer.name: tNetworkEgressFCQGrpPolicer
tNetworkEgressFCQGrpPolicer.description: The value of tNetworkEgressFCQGrpPolicer specifies the policer from queue-group to be used for packets in this forwarding class.

tNetworkQueuePolicyEHWrrPlcy.name: tNetworkQueuePolicyEHWrrPlcy
tNetworkQueuePolicyEHWrrPlcy.description: The value of tNetworkQueuePolicyEHWrrPlcy specifies the Weighted Round Robin (WRR) policy to use on this HSMDA egress queue.

tNetworkQueuePolicyEHPktBOffst.name: tNetworkQueuePolicyEHPktBOffst
tNetworkQueuePolicyEHPktBOffst.description: The value of tNetworkQueuePolicyEHPktBOffst specifies the packet byte offset to use for the HSMDA egress queues. This value is used for the adjustment to make to the size of each packet for HSMDA queue accounting.

tNetworkQueue.name: tNetworkQueue
tNetworkQueue.description: The queue ID is used as the secondary index to the table entry.

tNetworkQueueRowStatus.name: tNetworkQueueRowStatus
tNetworkQueueRowStatus.description: Row Status of the entry. This allows creation/deletion of rows in this table.

tNetworkQueuePoolName.name: tNetworkQueuePoolName
tNetworkQueuePoolName.description: The tNetworkQueuePoolName specifies the pool that is associated with this network queue. If tNetworkQueuePoolName is empty, no pool has been associated with the queue.

tNetworkQueueParent.name: tNetworkQueueParent
tNetworkQueueParent.description: The scheduler to which this queue would be feeding to.

tNetworkQueueLevel.name: tNetworkQueueLevel
tNetworkQueueLevel.description: This specifies the level of priority while feeding to the parent.

tNetworkQueueWeight.name: tNetworkQueueWeight
tNetworkQueueWeight.description: The weight that needs to be used by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding to.

tNetworkQueueCIRLevel.name: tNetworkQueueCIRLevel
tNetworkQueueCIRLevel.description: This specifies the level of priority while feeding to the parent. The level '0' means treat all offered load for this queue as for the above CIR traffic.

tNetworkQueueCIRWeight.name: tNetworkQueueCIRWeight
tNetworkQueueCIRWeight.description: The weight that needs to be used until the committed rate by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding to.

tNetworkQueueMCast.name: tNetworkQueueMCast
tNetworkQueueMCast.description: This object specifies if this is a multicast queue or not.

tNetworkQueueExpedite.name: tNetworkQueueExpedite
tNetworkQueueExpedite.description: tNetworkQueueExpedite specifies the priority that this queue should be assigned by the hardware level schedulers. The value 'auto-expedited' implies that this attribute should be dynamically updated by looking at the forwarding classes mapping into this queue. In such a case the queue is treated as 'non-expedited' if there is even a single non-expedited forwarding class using this queue. This attribute is associated with the queue at the time of creation and cannot be modified thereafter.

tNetworkQueueCIR.name: tNetworkQueueCIR
tNetworkQueueCIR.description: The percentage of max rate allowed.

tNetworkQueuePIR.name: tNetworkQueuePIR
tNetworkQueuePIR.description: The percentage of max rate allowed.

tNetworkQueueCBS.name: tNetworkQueueCBS
tNetworkQueueCBS.description: The percentage of reserved buffer space for the queue, defined to two decimal places.

tNetworkQueueMBS.name: tNetworkQueueMBS
tNetworkQueueMBS.description: The percentage of reserved buffer space for the queue, defined to two decimal places.

tNetworkQueueHiPrioOnly.name: tNetworkQueueHiPrioOnly
tNetworkQueueHiPrioOnly.description: The percentage of buffer space for the queue, used exclusively by high priority packets.

tNetworkQueueLastChanged.name: tNetworkQueueLastChanged
tNetworkQueueLastChanged.description: The value of the object tNetworkQueueLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in tNetworkQueueTable.

tNetworkQueueUsePortParent.name: tNetworkQueueUsePortParent
tNetworkQueueUsePortParent.description: The value of the object tNetworkQueueUsePortParent specifies whether this queue is parented by a port-level scheduler. When the value is 'true', this network queue is parented by a port-level scheduler.

tNetworkQueuePortLvl.name: tNetworkQueuePortLvl
tNetworkQueuePortLvl.description: The value of the object tNetworkQueuePortLvl specifies the port priority this queue will use to receive bandwidth from the port-level scheduler for its above-cir offered load.

tNetworkQueuePortWght.name: tNetworkQueuePortWght
tNetworkQueuePortWght.description: The value of the object tNetworkQueuePortWght specifies the weight this queue will use to receive bandwidth from the port-level scheduler for its above-cir offered load.

tNetworkQueuePortCIRLvl.name: tNetworkQueuePortCIRLvl
tNetworkQueuePortCIRLvl.description: The value of the object tNetworkQueuePortCIRLvl specifies the port priority this queue will use to receive bandwidth from the port-level scheduler for its within-cir offered load.

tNetworkQueuePortCIRWght.name: tNetworkQueuePortCIRWght
tNetworkQueuePortCIRWght.description: The value of the object tNetworkQueuePortCIRWght specifies the weight this queue will use to receive bandwidth from the port-level scheduler for its within-cir offered load.

tNetworkQueuePortAvgOverhead.name: tNetworkQueuePortAvgOverhead
tNetworkQueuePortAvgOverhead.description: The value of tNetworkQueuePortAvgOverhead specifies the encapsulation overhead, in hundredths of a percent, used to translate packet-based rate to frame-based rate and vice versa.

tNetworkQueueCIRAdaptation.name: tNetworkQueueCIRAdaptation
tNetworkQueueCIRAdaptation.description: The value of tNetworkQueueCIRAdaptation specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational CIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational value while maintaining the minimum offset.

tNetworkQueuePIRAdaptation.name: tNetworkQueuePIRAdaptation
tNetworkQueuePIRAdaptation.description: The value of tNetworkQueuePIRAdaptation specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational PIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational value while maintaining the minimum offset.

tNetworkQueueFC.name: tNetworkQueueFC
tNetworkQueueFC.description: The specific queue to be used for packets in this forwarding class.

tNetworkQueueFCMCast.name: tNetworkQueueFCMCast
tNetworkQueueFCMCast.description: The specific multicast queue to be used for packets in this forwarding class. The queue is used only for specific entities and will be ignored wherever it is irrelevant.

tNetworkQueueFCLastChanged.name: tNetworkQueueFCLastChanged
tNetworkQueueFCLastChanged.description: timestamp of last change to this row in tNetworkQueueFCTable.

tNetworkQueueFCEgrHsmdaQueue.name: tNetworkQueueFCEgrHsmdaQueue
tNetworkQueueFCEgrHsmdaQueue.description: The value of tNetworkQueueFCEgrHsmdaQueue specifies the egress hsmda queue to be used for packets in this forwarding class. This is only applicable on supported hsmda ports.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTblLastChgd.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTblLastChgd
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTblLastChgd.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTblLastChgd indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTable.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTable.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTable
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTable.description: The tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueTable contains the information about all network egress policies on HSMDA queues. Entries in this table are created whenever a network queue policy is created in tNetworkQueuePolicyEntry.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueEntry.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueEntry
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueEntry.description: Each entry in tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueEntry represents the information about a particular HSMDA queue for a network egress policy specified by tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueue.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueue.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueue
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueue.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueue indicates the HSMDA queue ID used as the secondary index to the table entry.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueuePIRPercent.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueuePIRPercent
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueuePIRPercent.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueuePIRPercent specifies the queue's PIR expressed as a percentage of port line rate.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueuePIRAdaptn.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueuePIRAdaptn
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueuePIRAdaptn.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueuePIRAdaptn specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational PIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueWrrWeight.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueWrrWeight
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueWrrWeight.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueWrrWeight specifies the weight with which this queue should parent into the HSMDA scheduler, provided it is not superseded by the Weighted Round Robin (WRR) policy. The weight of each queue determines how much bandwidth that queue gets out of the total rate for the scheduling class.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueMBS.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueMBS
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueMBS.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueMBS specifies the maximum amount of buffer space, in bytes, allowed for this network egress HSMDA queue.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueSlopePolicy.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueSlopePolicy
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueSlopePolicy.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueSlopePolicy specifies the slope policy on this network egress HSMDA queue. The slope policy defines the WRED slope behavior for this queue.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueLastChanged.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueLastChanged
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueLastChanged.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime for the last change to this row.

tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueBurstLimit.name: tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueBurstLimit
tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueBurstLimit.description: The value of tNetworkEgrHsmdaQueueBurstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the queue.

tSharedQueuePolicyTable.name: tSharedQueuePolicyTable
tSharedQueuePolicyTable.description: Defines the Alcatel-Lucent SROS series Shared Queue Policy Table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of defining the queue policies. tSharedQueuePolicyTable holds a list of all shared queue policies in the managed system. Shared queue policies should exist in this table before being referenced elsewhere. There is a default queue policy 'default' created by the agent and can not be deleted.

tSharedQueuePolicyEntry.name: tSharedQueuePolicyEntry
tSharedQueuePolicyEntry.description: Defines an entry in the tSharedQueuePolicyTable. Entries are created and deleted in this table by SNMP sets to tSharedQueuePolicyRowStatus.

tSharedQueuePolicy.name: tSharedQueuePolicy
tSharedQueuePolicy.description: tSharedQueuePolicy serves as an index and uniquely identifies a queue policy in the managed system.

tSharedQueuePolicyRowStatus.name: tSharedQueuePolicyRowStatus
tSharedQueuePolicyRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
tSharedQueuePolicyRowStatus.description: tSharedQueuePolicyRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tSharedQueuePolicyTable. The deletion of an entry in this table will fail if the action is performed on the default policy or the policy is being used within the system.

tSharedQueuePolicyLastChanged.name: tSharedQueuePolicyLastChanged
tSharedQueuePolicyLastChanged.description: tSharedQueuePolicyLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime when the queue policy entry was last modified.

tSharedQueuePolicyDescription.name: tSharedQueuePolicyDescription
tSharedQueuePolicyDescription.description: tSharedQueuePolicyDescription specifies the user provided description string for this queue policy entry. It can consist of only the printable, seven-bit ASCII characters.

tSharedQueueTable.name: tSharedQueueTable
tSharedQueueTable.description: Defines the Alcatel-Lucent SROS series Shared Queue Table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of defining the queues for the shared queue policies existing in the tSharedQueuePolicyTable. tSharedQueueTable holds a list of all the shared queues in the managed system defined for the queue policies. Queues should exist in this table before being referenced by the forwarding class mappings within the queue policy as defined in the tSharedQueueFCTable. There is a default queue with the queue identifier '1' which gets created automatically when a new queue policy is created.

tSharedQueueEntry.name: tSharedQueueEntry
tSharedQueueEntry.description: Defines an entry in the tSharedQueueTable. Entries are created/deleted in this table by SNMP sets to tSharedQueueRowStatus. An exception to this rule is the default queue. The default queue is created/deleted as a result of the creation/deletion of a new queue policy in the tSharedQueuePolicyTable.

tSharedQueueId.name: tSharedQueueId
tSharedQueueId.description: tSharedQueueId serves as the secondary index. When used in conjunction with tSharedQueuePolicy, it uniquely identifies a shared queue in the managed system.

tSharedQueueRowStatus.name: tSharedQueueRowStatus
tSharedQueueRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
tSharedQueueRowStatus.description: tSharedQueueRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tSharedQueueTable. The deletion of an entry in this table will fail if the action is performed on the default queue or if the queue is being referenced by a forwarding class mapping in the queue policy.

tSharedQueueLastChanged.name: tSharedQueueLastChanged
tSharedQueueLastChanged.description: tSharedQueueLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime when the queue entry was last modified.

tSharedQueuePoolName.name: tSharedQueuePoolName
tSharedQueuePoolName.description: tSharedQueuePoolName specifies the pool from which the queue should be allocating its buffer. By default it will share the default pool being used by the entity where the queue is instantiated.

tSharedQueueParent.name: tSharedQueueParent
tSharedQueueParent.description: tSharedQueueParent specifies the scheduler to which this queue should be feeding into. By default there would be no parent for the queue and it will be controlled by the entity where the queue is instantiated.

tSharedQueueLevel.name: tSharedQueueLevel
tSharedQueueLevel.description: tSharedQueueLevel specifies the level of priority to be used by the parent entity to compute the priority of this queue when the traffic is exceeding the committed rate.

tSharedQueueWeight.name: tSharedQueueWeight
tSharedQueueWeight.description: tSharedQueueWeight specifies the weight that this queue should be assigned by the parent among all the entities feeding into the parent with the same level when the traffic is exceeding the committed rate.

tSharedQueueCIRLevel.name: tSharedQueueCIRLevel
tSharedQueueCIRLevel.description: tSharedQueueCIRLevel specifies the level of priority to be used by the parent entity to compute the priority of this queue when the traffic is conforming to the committed rate. The level '0' means treat all offered load for this queue same as the load which is exceeding the committed rate.

tSharedQueueCIRWeight.name: tSharedQueueCIRWeight
tSharedQueueCIRWeight.description: tSharedQueueCIRWeight specifies the weight that this queue should be assigned by the parent among all the entities feeding into the parent with the same level when the traffic is conforming to the committed rate.

tSharedQueueExpedite.name: tSharedQueueExpedite
tSharedQueueExpedite.description: tSharedQueueExpedite specifies the priority that this queue should be assigned by the hardware level schedulers. The value 'auto-expedited' implies that this attribute should be dynamically updated by looking at the forwarding classes mapping into this queue. In such a case the queue is treated as 'non-expedited' if there is even a single non-expedited forwarding class using this queue.

tSharedQueueCIR.name: tSharedQueueCIR
tSharedQueueCIR.description: tSharedQueueCIR specifies the committed rate as a percentage of maximum rate for this queue.

tSharedQueuePIR.name: tSharedQueuePIR
tSharedQueuePIR.description: tSharedQueuePIR specifies the peak rate as a percentage of maximum rate for this queue.

tSharedQueueCBS.name: tSharedQueueCBS
tSharedQueueCBS.description: tSharedQueueCBS specifies the committed burst size as a percentage of maximum reserved buffer space for the queue.

tSharedQueueMBS.name: tSharedQueueMBS
tSharedQueueMBS.description: tSharedQueueMBS specifies the maximum burst size as a percentage of maximum reserved buffer space for the queue.

tSharedQueueHiPrioOnly.name: tSharedQueueHiPrioOnly
tSharedQueueHiPrioOnly.description: tSharedQueueHiPrioOnly specifies the percentage of buffer space to be exclusively by high priority packets as a percentage of maximum reserved buffer space for the queue.

tSharedQueueIsMultipoint.name: tSharedQueueIsMultipoint
tSharedQueueIsMultipoint.description: The value of tSharedQueueIsMultipoint specifies whether this shared queue is a multipoint-shared queue. This object can only be modified at row creation time; any attempt to set it after creation is silently ignored.

tSharedQueueFCTable.name: tSharedQueueFCTable
tSharedQueueFCTable.description: Defines the Alcatel-Lucent SROS series forwarding class to shared queue mapping table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of defining the forwarding class to shared queue mapping for the queue policies existing in the tSharedQueuePolicyTable. tSharedQueueFCTable holds a list of forwarding class to queue mappings managed system defined for the queue policies. The forwarding classes which are not existing in this table should use the default shared queue for this policy.

tSharedQueueFCEntry.name: tSharedQueueFCEntry
tSharedQueueFCEntry.description: Defines an entry in the tSharedQueueFCTable. Entries are created/deleted in this table by SNMP sets to tSharedQueueFCRowStatus.

tSharedQueueFCName.name: tSharedQueueFCName
tSharedQueueFCName.description: tSharedQueueFCName serves as the secondary index. When used in conjunction with tSharedQueuePolicy, it uniquely identifies a forwarding class to queue mapping in the managed system.

tSharedQueueFCRowStatus.name: tSharedQueueFCRowStatus
tSharedQueueFCRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
tSharedQueueFCRowStatus.description: tSharedQueueFCRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tSharedQueueFCTable. Deletion of an entry from this table will cause the forwarding class to use the default mapping.

tSharedQueueFCLastChanged.name: tSharedQueueFCLastChanged
tSharedQueueFCLastChanged.description: tSharedQueueFCLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime when the forwarding class to queue mapping entry was last modified.

tSharedQueueFCQueue.name: tSharedQueueFCQueue
tSharedQueueFCQueue.description: tSharedQueueFCQueue specifies the logical queue that the traffic classified into this forwarding class should use.

tSharedQueueFCMCastQueue.name: tSharedQueueFCMCastQueue
tSharedQueueFCMCastQueue.description: The value of tSharedQueueFCMCastQueue specifies the logical queue that mutlticast traffic classified into this forwarding class should use.

tSharedQueueFCBCastQueue.name: tSharedQueueFCBCastQueue
tSharedQueueFCBCastQueue.description: The value of tSharedQueueFCBCastQueue specifies the logical queue that broadscast traffic classified into this forwarding class should use.

tSharedQueueFCUnknownQueue.name: tSharedQueueFCUnknownQueue
tSharedQueueFCUnknownQueue.description: The value of tSharedQueueFCUnknownQueue specifies the logical queue that unknown traffic classified into this forwarding class should use.

tQosIngQGroupTableLastChanged.name: tQosIngQGroupTableLastChanged
tQosIngQGroupTableLastChanged.description: tQosIngQGroupTableLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to the tQosIngQGroupTable.

tQosIngQGroupTable.name: tQosIngQGroupTable
tQosIngQGroupTable.description: tQosIngQGroupTable defines Ingress Queue Group Table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of defining the queue groups for the queues existing in the tQosIngQueueTable. tQosIngQGroupTable holds a list of all the queue-groups in the managed system defined. Queue-groups should exist in this table before being referenced by the forwarding class mappings within the queue policy as defined in the tSapIngressFCTable.

tQosIngQGroupEntry.name: tQosIngQGroupEntry
tQosIngQGroupEntry.description: tQosIngQGroupEntry defines an entry in the tQosIngQGroupTable. Entries are created/deleted in this table by SNMP sets to tQosIngQGroupRowStatus.

tQosIngQGroupName.name: tQosIngQGroupName
tQosIngQGroupName.description: tQosIngQGroupName defines the Ingress Queue Group name. It uniquely identifies an ingress queue group in the managed system.

tQosIngQGroupRowStatus.name: tQosIngQGroupRowStatus
tQosIngQGroupRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
tQosIngQGroupRowStatus.description: tQosIngQGroupRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tQosIngQGroupTable. The deletion of an entry in this table will fail if the queue is being referenced by a forwarding class mapping in the queue policy.

tQosIngQGroupLastChanged.name: tQosIngQGroupLastChanged
tQosIngQGroupLastChanged.description: tQosIngQGroupLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime when the queue entry was last modified.

tQosIngQGroupDescr.name: tQosIngQGroupDescr
tQosIngQGroupDescr.description: tQosIngQGroupDescr specifies the description of the queue-group.

tQosIngQTableLastChanged.name: tQosIngQTableLastChanged
tQosIngQTableLastChanged.description: tQosIngQTableLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to the tQosIngQueueTable.

tQosIngQueueEntry.name: tQosIngQueueEntry
tQosIngQueueEntry.description: tQosIngQueueEntry defines a particular ingress queue. Entries are created by user by setting tQosIngQueueRowStatus.

tQosIngQueue.name: tQosIngQueue
tQosIngQueue.description: tQosIngQueue specifies the queue ID which is used as the secondary index to the table entry.

tQosIngQueueRowStatus.name: tQosIngQueueRowStatus
tQosIngQueueRowStatus.description: tQosIngQueueRowStatus is the Row-Status of the entry. This allows creation/deletion of rows in this table.

tQosIngQueueParent.name: tQosIngQueueParent
tQosIngQueueParent.description: tQosIngQueueParent specifies the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding.

tQosIngQueueLevel.name: tQosIngQueueLevel
tQosIngQueueLevel.description: tQosIngQueueLevel specifies the level of priority while feeding the parent.

tQosIngQueueWeight.name: tQosIngQueueWeight
tQosIngQueueWeight.description: tQosIngQueueWeight specifies the weight that needs to be used by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding.

tQosIngQueueCIRLevel.name: tQosIngQueueCIRLevel
tQosIngQueueCIRLevel.description: tQosIngQueueCIRLevel specifies the level of priority while feeding to the parent. The level '0' means treat all offered load for this queue as for the above CIR traffic.

tQosIngQueueCIRWeight.name: tQosIngQueueCIRWeight
tQosIngQueueCIRWeight.description: tQosIngQueueCIRWeight specifies the weight that needs to be used until the committed rate by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding.

tQosIngQueueMCast.name: tQosIngQueueMCast
tQosIngQueueMCast.description: tQosIngQueueMCast specifies if this is a multicast queue.

tQosIngQueueExpedite.name: tQosIngQueueExpedite
tQosIngQueueExpedite.description: tQosIngQueueExpedite specifies the priority that this queue should be assigned by the hardware level schedulers. This attribute is associated with the queue at the time of creation and cannot be modified thereafter.

tQosIngQueueCBS.name: tQosIngQueueCBS
tQosIngQueueCBS.description: tQosIngQueueCBS specifies the amount of reserved buffer space for the queue.

tQosIngQueueMBS.name: tQosIngQueueMBS
tQosIngQueueMBS.description: tQosIngQueueMBS specifies the maximum amount of buffer space allowed for the queue. This object has been replaced with tQosIngQueueMBSBytes object.

tQosIngQueueHiPrioOnly.name: tQosIngQueueHiPrioOnly
tQosIngQueueHiPrioOnly.description: tQosIngQueueHiPrioOnly specifies the percentage of buffer space for the queue, used exclusively by high priority packets.

tQosIngQueuePIRAdaptation.name: tQosIngQueuePIRAdaptation
tQosIngQueuePIRAdaptation.description: tQosIngQueuePIRAdaptation specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational PIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset.

tQosIngQueueCIRAdaptation.name: tQosIngQueueCIRAdaptation
tQosIngQueueCIRAdaptation.description: tQosIngQueueCIRAdaptation specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational CIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset.

tQosIngQueueAdminPIR.name: tQosIngQueueAdminPIR
tQosIngQueueAdminPIR.description: tQosIngQueueAdminPIR specifies the administrative PIR specified by the user.

tQosIngQueueAdminCIR.name: tQosIngQueueAdminCIR
tQosIngQueueAdminCIR.description: tQosIngQueueAdminCIR specifies the administrative CIR specified by the user.

tQosIngQueueLastChanged.name: tQosIngQueueLastChanged
tQosIngQueueLastChanged.description: tQosIngQueueLastChanged specifies the timestamp of last change to this row in tQosIngQueueTable.

tQosIngQueuePoliced.name: tQosIngQueuePoliced
tQosIngQueuePoliced.description: tQosIngQueuePoliced specifies that the out of profile traffic feeding into the physical queue instance should be dropped. tQosIngQueuePoliced overrides the bandwidth specified by the object tQosIngQueueAdminCIR.

tQosIngQueueMode.name: tQosIngQueueMode
tQosIngQueueMode.description: tQosIngQueueMode specifies the mode in which the queue is operating. This attribute is associated with the queue at the time of creation and cannot be modified thereafter.

tQosIngQueuePoolName.name: tQosIngQueuePoolName
tQosIngQueuePoolName.description: tQosIngQueuePoolName specifies the name of the pool to be applied for the ingress queue.

tQosIngQueueMBSBytes.name: tQosIngQueueMBSBytes
tQosIngQueueMBSBytes.description: tQosIngQueueMBSBytes specifies the maximum amount of buffer space allowed for the queue.

tQosIngQueueBurstLimit.name: tQosIngQueueBurstLimit
tQosIngQueueBurstLimit.description: The value of tQosIngQueueBurstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of a queue.

tQosIngQueueAdvCfgPolicy.name: tQosIngQueueAdvCfgPolicy
tQosIngQueueAdvCfgPolicy.description: The value of tQosIngQueueAdvCfgPolicy specifies the name of the advanced configuration policy to be applied with this queue.

tQosEgrQGroupTableLastChanged.name: tQosEgrQGroupTableLastChanged
tQosEgrQGroupTableLastChanged.description: tQosEgrQGroupTableLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to the tQosEgrQGroupTable.

tQosEgrQGroupTable.name: tQosEgrQGroupTable
tQosEgrQGroupTable.description: tQosEgrQGroupTable defines the Ingress Queue Group Table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of defining the queue groups for the queues existing in the tQosEgrQueueTable. tQosEgrQGroupTable holds a list of all the queue-groups in the managed system defined. Queue-groups should exist in this table before being referenced by the forwarding class mappings within the queue policy as defined in the tSapIngressFCTable.

tQosEgrQGroupEntry.name: tQosEgrQGroupEntry
tQosEgrQGroupEntry.description: tQosEgrQGroupEntry defines an entry in the tQosEgrQGroupTable. Entries are created/deleted in this table by SNMP sets to tQosEgrQGroupRowStatus.

tQosEgrQGroupName.name: tQosEgrQGroupName
tQosEgrQGroupName.description: tQosEgrQGroupName defines the Ingress Queue Group name. It uniquely identifies an ingress queue group in the managed system.

tQosEgrQGroupRowStatus.name: tQosEgrQGroupRowStatus
tQosEgrQGroupRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
tQosEgrQGroupRowStatus.description: tQosEgrQGroupRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tQosEgrQGroupTable. The deletion of an entry in this table will fail if the queue is being referenced by a forwarding class mapping in the queue policy.

tQosEgrQGroupLastChanged.name: tQosEgrQGroupLastChanged
tQosEgrQGroupLastChanged.description: tQosEgrQGroupLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime when the queue entry was last modified.

tQosEgrQGroupDescr.name: tQosEgrQGroupDescr
tQosEgrQGroupDescr.description: tQosEgrQGroupDescr specifies the description of the queue-group.

tQosEgrQTableLastChanged.name: tQosEgrQTableLastChanged
tQosEgrQTableLastChanged.description: tQosEgrQTableLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to the tQosEgrQueueTable.

tQosEgrQueueEntry.name: tQosEgrQueueEntry
tQosEgrQueueEntry.description: tQosEgrQueueEntry defines a particular egress queue. Entries are created and deleted by user.

tQosEgrQueue.name: tQosEgrQueue
tQosEgrQueue.description: The value of tQosEgrQueue identifies the queue index which is used as the second index to the table entry. Zero is not allowed.

tQosEgrQueueRowStatus.name: tQosEgrQueueRowStatus
tQosEgrQueueRowStatus.description: This is the Row Status of the entry. This allows creation/deletion of rows in this table.

tQosEgrQueueParent.name: tQosEgrQueueParent
tQosEgrQueueParent.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueParent specifies the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding.

tQosEgrQueueLevel.name: tQosEgrQueueLevel
tQosEgrQueueLevel.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueLevel specifies the level of priority while feeding the parent.

tQosEgrQueueWeight.name: tQosEgrQueueWeight
tQosEgrQueueWeight.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueWeight specifies the weight that needs to be used by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding.

tQosEgrQueueCIRLevel.name: tQosEgrQueueCIRLevel
tQosEgrQueueCIRLevel.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueCIRLevel specifies the level of priority while feeding the parent. The level '0' means treat all offered load for this queue as for the above CIR traffic.

tQosEgrQueueCIRWeight.name: tQosEgrQueueCIRWeight
tQosEgrQueueCIRWeight.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueCIRWeight specifies the weight that needs to be used until the committed rate by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding.

tQosEgrQueueExpedite.name: tQosEgrQueueExpedite
tQosEgrQueueExpedite.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueExpedite specifies the priority that this queue should be assigned by the hardware level schedulers.

tQosEgrQueueCBS.name: tQosEgrQueueCBS
tQosEgrQueueCBS.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueCBS specifies the amount of reserved buffer space for the queue.

tQosEgrQueueMBS.name: tQosEgrQueueMBS
tQosEgrQueueMBS.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueMBS specifies the maximum amount of buffer space allowed for the queue. This object has been replaced with tQosEgrQueueMBSBytes object.

tQosEgrQueueHiPrioOnly.name: tQosEgrQueueHiPrioOnly
tQosEgrQueueHiPrioOnly.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueHiPrioOnly specifies the percentage of buffer space for the queue, used exclusively by high priority packets.

tQosEgrQueuePIRAdaptation.name: tQosEgrQueuePIRAdaptation
tQosEgrQueuePIRAdaptation.description: The value of tQosEgrQueuePIRAdaptation specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational PIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset.

tQosEgrQueueCIRAdaptation.name: tQosEgrQueueCIRAdaptation
tQosEgrQueueCIRAdaptation.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueCIRAdaptation specifies the adaptation rule to be used while computing the operational CIR value. The adaptation rule specifies the rules to compute the operational values while maintaining minimum offset.

tQosEgrQueueAdminPIR.name: tQosEgrQueueAdminPIR
tQosEgrQueueAdminPIR.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueAdminPIR specifies the administrative PIR. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if tQosEgrQueueAdminPIR is set to non-default value when the object tQosEgrQueueRateType is set to 'percent'.

tQosEgrQueueAdminCIR.name: tQosEgrQueueAdminCIR
tQosEgrQueueAdminCIR.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueAdminCIR specifies the administrative CIR. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if tQosEgrQueueAdminCIR is set to non-default value when the object tQosEgrQueueRateType is set to 'percent'.

tQosEgrQueueLastChanged.name: tQosEgrQueueLastChanged
tQosEgrQueueLastChanged.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in tQosEgrQueueTable.

tQosEgrQueueUsePortParent.name: tQosEgrQueueUsePortParent
tQosEgrQueueUsePortParent.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueUsePortParent specifies whether this queue is parented by a port-level scheduler. When the value is 'true', this SAP egress queue is parented by a port-level scheduler. This object is mutually exclusive with tQosEgrQueueParent. Only one kind of parent is allowed.

tQosEgrQueuePortLvl.name: tQosEgrQueuePortLvl
tQosEgrQueuePortLvl.description: The value of the object tQosEgrQueuePortLvl specifies the port priority this queue will use to receive bandwidth from the port-level scheduler for its above-cir offered load.

tQosEgrQueuePortWght.name: tQosEgrQueuePortWght
tQosEgrQueuePortWght.description: The value of the object tQosEgrQueuePortWght specifies the weight this queue will use to receive bandwidth from the port-level scheduler for its above-cir offered load.

tQosEgrQueuePortCIRLvl.name: tQosEgrQueuePortCIRLvl
tQosEgrQueuePortCIRLvl.description: The value of the object tQosEgrQueuePortCIRLvl specifies the port priority this queue will use to receive bandwidth from the port-level scheduler for its within-cir offered load.

tQosEgrQueuePortCIRWght.name: tQosEgrQueuePortCIRWght
tQosEgrQueuePortCIRWght.description: The value of the object tQosEgrQueuePortCIRWght specifies the weight this queue will use to receive bandwidth from the port-level scheduler for its within-cir offered load.

tQosEgrQueuePoolName.name: tQosEgrQueuePoolName
tQosEgrQueuePoolName.description: The value of tQosEgrQueuePoolName specifies the name of the pool to be applied for SAP egress queue.

tQosEgrQueueXPWredQ.name: tQosEgrQueueXPWredQ
tQosEgrQueueXPWredQ.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueXPWredQ specifies whether to alter the generic pool association of the queue for the purpose of allowing queue-specific WRED slopes with minimal provisioning.

tQosEgrQueueXPWredQSlope.name: tQosEgrQueueXPWredQSlope
tQosEgrQueueXPWredQSlope.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueXPWredQSlope specifies the name of the slope-policy to be applied for QOS egress queue. When tQosEgrQueueXPWredQ has the value 'false', an 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if an attempt is made to set this object to a value other than 'default'.

tQosEgrQueueMBSBytes.name: tQosEgrQueueMBSBytes
tQosEgrQueueMBSBytes.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueMBSBytes specifies the maximum amount of buffer space allowed for the queue.

tQosEgrQueueAdminPIRPercent.name: tQosEgrQueueAdminPIRPercent
tQosEgrQueueAdminPIRPercent.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueAdminPIRPercent specifies the administrative PIR percentage, in hudredths of a percent. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if tQosEgrQueueAdminPIRPercent is set to non-default value when the object tQosEgrQueueRateType is set to 'kbps'.

tQosEgrQueueAdminCIRPercent.name: tQosEgrQueueAdminCIRPercent
tQosEgrQueueAdminCIRPercent.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueAdminCIRPercent specifies the administrative CIR percentage, in hudredths of a percent. An 'inconsistentValue' error is returned if tQosEgrQueueAdminCIRPercent is set to non-default value when the object tQosEgrQueueRateType is set to 'kbps'.

tQosEgrQueueRateType.name: tQosEgrQueueRateType
tQosEgrQueueRateType.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueRateType specifies the type of Egress queue rate. When the value of the object is set to 'kbps', the egresss queue rates are specified in kbps. The objects tQosEgrQueueAdminCIRPercent and tQosEgrQueueAdminPIRPercent will be set to their default values. When the value of the object is set to 'percent', the egress queue rates are specified in percentage. The objects tQosEgrQueueAdminCIR and tQosEgrQueueAdminPIR will be set to their default values.

tQosEgrQueueBurstLimit.name: tQosEgrQueueBurstLimit
tQosEgrQueueBurstLimit.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueBurstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of a queue.

tQosEgrQueueAdvCfgPolicy.name: tQosEgrQueueAdvCfgPolicy
tQosEgrQueueAdvCfgPolicy.description: The value of tQosEgrQueueAdvCfgPolicy specifies the name of the advanced configuration policy to be applied with this queue.

tQosEgrQueuePktOffset.name: tQosEgrQueuePktOffset
tQosEgrQueuePktOffset.description: The value of tQosEgrQueuePktOffset specifies the packet byte offset to be applied with this queue.

tQosEgrQGroupFCTableLastChanged.name: tQosEgrQGroupFCTableLastChanged
tQosEgrQGroupFCTableLastChanged.description: The value of tQosEgrQGroupFCTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of an entry in the tQosEgrQGroupFCTable. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tQosEgrQGroupFCTable.name: tQosEgrQGroupFCTable
tQosEgrQGroupFCTable.description: This table maintains the information of forwarding classes in a egress queue group.

tQosEgrQGroupFCEntry.name: tQosEgrQGroupFCEntry
tQosEgrQGroupFCEntry.description: Information about a particular queue group's forwarding class.

tQosEgrQGroupFCName.name: tQosEgrQGroupFCName
tQosEgrQGroupFCName.description: The value of the object tQosEgrQGroupFCName specifies the name of the forwarding class

tQosEgrQGroupFCRowStatus.name: tQosEgrQGroupFCRowStatus
tQosEgrQGroupFCRowStatus.description: The value of tQosEgrQGroupFCRowStatus specifies the Row Status for this entry.

tQosEgrQGroupFCLastChanged.name: tQosEgrQGroupFCLastChanged
tQosEgrQGroupFCLastChanged.description: The value of tQosEgrQGroupFCLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in tQosEgrQGroupFCTable.

tQosEgrQGroupFCQueue.name: tQosEgrQGroupFCQueue
tQosEgrQGroupFCQueue.description: The value of tQosEgrQGroupFCQueue specifies the queue to be used for the packets in this forwarding class.

tSlopePolicyTable.name: tSlopePolicyTable
tSlopePolicyTable.description: Slope Policy Table. Each entry in this table defines the RED slopes for the high and the low priority traffic.

tSlopePolicy.name: tSlopePolicy
tSlopePolicy.description: tSlopePolicy maintains the name of the slope policy identifying the policy.

tSlopeRowStatus.name: tSlopeRowStatus
tSlopeRowStatus.description: Row Status of the entry. This allows creation/deletion of rows in this table.

tSlopeHiAdminStatus.name: tSlopeHiAdminStatus
tSlopeHiAdminStatus.description: tSlopeHiAdminStatus specifies the admin state for the high priority RED slope. If the tSlopeHiAdminStatus is set to 'down', the RED slope is inactive.

tSlopeHiStartAverage.name: tSlopeHiStartAverage
tSlopeHiStartAverage.description: The percentage of the buffer utilized after which the drop probability starts to rise above 0.

tSlopeHiMaxAverage.name: tSlopeHiMaxAverage
tSlopeHiMaxAverage.description: The percentage of the buffer utilized after which the drop probability is 100 percent. This implies that all packets beyond this point will be dropped.

tSlopeHiMaxProbability.name: tSlopeHiMaxProbability
tSlopeHiMaxProbability.description: The drop probability increases steadily from 0 at the tSlopeHiStartAverage upto the tSlopeHiMaxProbability at the tSlopeHiMaxAverage.

tSlopeLoAdminStatus.name: tSlopeLoAdminStatus
tSlopeLoAdminStatus.description: tSlopeLoAdminStatus specifies the admin state for the high priority RED slope. If the tSlopeLoAdminStatus is set to 'down', the RED slope is inactive.

tSlopeLoStartAverage.name: tSlopeLoStartAverage
tSlopeLoStartAverage.description: The percentage of the buffer utilized after which the drop probability starts to rise above 0.

tSlopeLoMaxAverage.name: tSlopeLoMaxAverage
tSlopeLoMaxAverage.description: The percentage of the buffer utilized after which the drop probability is 100 percent. This implies that all packets beyond this point will be dropped.

tSlopeLoMaxProbability.name: tSlopeLoMaxProbability
tSlopeLoMaxProbability.description: The drop probability increases steadily from 0 at the tSlopeLoStartAverage upto the tSlopeLoMaxProbability at the tSlopeLoMaxAverage.

tSlopeTimeAvgFactor.name: tSlopeTimeAvgFactor
tSlopeTimeAvgFactor.description: The time average factor describes the weighting between the previous shared buffer average utilization result and the new shared buffer utilization in determining the new shared buffer average utilization.

tSlopeLastChanged.name: tSlopeLastChanged
tSlopeLastChanged.description: Timestamp of when this entry was last changed.

tHsmdaSlopePolicyTable.name: tHsmdaSlopePolicyTable
tHsmdaSlopePolicyTable.description: The tHsmdaSlopePolicyTable has an entry for each HSMDA slope policy configured on this system.

tHsmdaSlopePolicyEntry.name: tHsmdaSlopePolicyEntry
tHsmdaSlopePolicyEntry.description: Each row represents a particular HSMDA slope policy. Entries are created and deleted by the user.

tHsmdaSlopePolicyName.name: tHsmdaSlopePolicyName
tHsmdaSlopePolicyName.description: The value of tHsmdaSlopePolicyName specifies the name of the HSMDA slope policy.

tHsmdaSlopePolicyRowStatus.name: tHsmdaSlopePolicyRowStatus
tHsmdaSlopePolicyRowStatus.description: The value of tHsmdaSlopePolicyRowStatus is used for the creation and deletion of HSMDA slope policies.

tHsmdaSlopeLastChanged.name: tHsmdaSlopeLastChanged
tHsmdaSlopeLastChanged.description: The value of tHsmdaSlopeLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tHsmdaSlopeDescription.name: tHsmdaSlopeDescription
tHsmdaSlopeDescription.description: The value of tHsmdaSlopeDescription specifies the description of this HSMDA slope policy.

tHsmdaSlopeQueueMbs.name: tHsmdaSlopeQueueMbs
tHsmdaSlopeQueueMbs.description: The value of tHsmdaSlopeQueueMbs specifies the maximum amount of buffer space, in bytes, allowed for any HSMDA queue associated with this HSMDA slope policy. Specifying a value of 0 effectively disables all queues associated with this slope policy causing each queue to discard all packets. This object is obsoleted in 10.0 Release.

tHsmdaSlopeHiAdminStatus.name: tHsmdaSlopeHiAdminStatus
tHsmdaSlopeHiAdminStatus.description: The value of tHsmdaSlopeHiAdminStatus specifies the admin state for the high priority RED slope. If the tHsmdaSlopeHiAdminStatus is set to 'disabled', the RED slope is inactive.

tHsmdaSlopeHiStartDepth.name: tHsmdaSlopeHiStartDepth
tHsmdaSlopeHiStartDepth.description: The value of tHsmdaSlopeHiStartDepth specifies the percentage of the buffer utilized after which the drop probability starts to rise above 0.

tHsmdaSlopeHiMaxDepth.name: tHsmdaSlopeHiMaxDepth
tHsmdaSlopeHiMaxDepth.description: The value of tHsmdaSlopeHiMaxDepth specifies the percentage of the buffer utilized after which the drop probability is 100 percent. This implies that all packets beyond this point will be dropped.

tHsmdaSlopeHiMaxProbability.name: tHsmdaSlopeHiMaxProbability
